cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.SY, quant-ph. 

The paper discusses the development of hidden quantum Markov models (HQMMs) to model stochastic processes, which involves probabilistic reasoning and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with control systems and optimization, which suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper is based on the quantum mechanical view of probability, which makes quant-ph (Quantum Physics) a possible sub-category as well.
